Who are we?

   The Food Observatory – ODELA is a well-established research group,
   associated with
   the University of Barcelona’s Department of Social Anthropology, that
   is interested in
   management of knowledge related to food and health.

   The Observatory is made up of a team of qualified researchers from
   various fields
   (anthropology, communication, economics, statistics, history,
   linguistics, nutrition and
   sociology), most of whom are associated with Catalan universities and
   social entities
   based in Barcelona. The team has extensive experience in the study of
   food practices
   and attitudes at all stages of the agri-food chain (production,
   distribution and
   consumption) and is at the service of economic and social actors.

   Since it was established, the Observatory has carried out and
   disseminated studies on
   ways of life, opinions, perceptions, aspirations, attitudes and
   consumption practices.
   Research is conducted using the most advanced methods (qualitative,
   quantitative,
   traditional and virtual ethnography).

   More information: Memoria Odela 2015 – 2018

   Statutes and governing body

Overall aim

   ODELA’s overall aim is to observe, describe, explain and interpret the
   variability and
   evolution of eating habits and behaviours in order to achieve a greater
   and better
   understanding of these phenomena. We take a critical approach that
   encompasses
   analysis of aspects related to health, the impact on food-producing
   societies, and the
   consequences that current food consumption habits have for ecosystems.

Specific objectives

     * To generate useful data and information for the academic community,
       social
       entities and government agencies.
     * To provide scientific and technical advice to not-for-profit
       organizations, food
       professionals, the media and public institutions interested in
       promoting policies
       related to food and nutrition.
     * To critically identify phenomena that generate undesirable effects
       for societies and
       ecosystems along the agri-food chain, and to analyse, disseminate
       and speak out
       against their causes.
     * To help public educational and healthcare institutions and social
       organizations
       respond more effectively to consumer needs.
     * To provide expert advice to citizens and consumer organizations,
       acting as
       advocates for a more satisfactory and healthier diet. We share our
       expertise with
       final consumers and with producers and actors throughout the
       agri-food chain.

Commitment

   ODELA works with government agencies, foundations, social entities,
   cooperatives,
   professional federations, territorial groups, consumer organizations
   and the media. For
   these groups and organizations, ODELA’s expertise in techniques for
   obtaining,
   processing, contextualizing and analysing information make it a
   guarantee of
   professionalism and experience.

Quality in scientific research

